eflecting that expectation, and with them, discount rates.=C2=A0
This dynamic hits the types of companies we talk about in Not Boring =E2=80=
=93 fast-growing technology companies, especially newer ones =E2=80=93 hard=
er than it hits more boring, predictable, slower-growing businesses. The si=
mplest explanation, based on the formula we=E2=80=99ve been talking about, =
is when these companies are expected to generate most of their cash flow: i=
n the future.=C2=A0
While there are variations on the theme, the typical tech company model is =
to raise venture capital, invest a ton of money upfront in technology and c=
ustomer acquisition, get super big, and then, and only then, pull back on f=
