What to Do When Belief Dries Up
Writing all of this out has given me a new perspective on all of the cost c=
utting measures and pivots to profitability in the tech and startup ecosyst=
em. On the surface, they look like survival tactics =E2=80=93 keep burn low=
 so you don=E2=80=99t run out of money while funding is harder to come by, =
get to profitability so you control your own destiny =E2=80=93 and they are=
, but they=E2=80=99re more than that. They=E2=80=99re the rational moves.=
=C2=A0
In this environment, cash flows next year are worth a lot more relative to =
cash flows in ten years than they were just a year ago. Cutting costs and m=
aking moves to get profitable sooner, even at the expense of long-term cash=
